{{Infobox language |name =Tetela |nativename =''Ɔtɛtɛla'' |states =[[Democratic Republic of the Congo]] |region =Northern [[Kasai-Oriental|Kasai Oriental Province]] |speakers =760,000 |date=1991 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2 =[[Atlantic–Congo languages|Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3 =[[Benue–Congo languages|Benue–Congo]] |fam4 =[[Bantoid languages|Bantoid]] |fam5 =[[Bantu languages|Bantu]] ([[Guthrie classification of Bantu languages#Zone C|Zone C]]) |fam6 =[[Tetela languages|Tetela]] (C.70) |fam7 = |lc1 =tll |ld1 = Tetela |lc2 = hba |ld2 = Hamba<!--per Maho 2009--> |glotto=tete1253 |glottoname=Tetela |glotto2=hamb1245 |glottoname2=Hamba |glottorefname2=Hamba de Lomela |guthrie=C.71 }}
'''Tetela''' (Otetela, Kitetela, Kikitatela), also ''Sungu'', is a [[Bantu languages|Bantu]] language of northern [[Kasai-Oriental]] Province, [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]]. It is spoken by the [[Tetela people]].
==Noun classes {{anchor|Noun classes}}== Like other [[Bantu languages]], Tetela [[grammar]] arranges nouns into a number of [[noun class|classes]]. The ancestral system had 22 classes (counting singular and plural as distinct according to the [[Carl Meinhof|Meinhof system]]), with most Bantu languages sharing at least ten of them.
